Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%can}; pat very dry with #paper towels{}.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%oz} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces (halve lengthwise first if carrots are on the larger side). Halve, peel, and slice @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb} until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4).

Toss chickpeas, carrots, and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp}, @curry powder{1%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until chickpeas are crispy and veggies are tender, ~{18-22%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add ginger, half the minced onion, ¾ tsp @garlic powder{1%tsp}, ¾ tsp @garam masala{1%tsp}, and a big pinch of salt (for 4 servings, use 1 1/2 tsp garlic powder and 1 1/2 tsp garam masala). (You'll use the rest of the garlic powder and garam masala later.) Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{2%units}, and ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4). Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While the rice cooks, pat @skin-on salmon{10%oz} dry with paper towels; season with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add salmon (skin sides down); cook salmon until skin is crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}, then flip and cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Red Pepper Chutney ==

Mince @cilantro{1/4%oz}; transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Add @red pepper jam{1}, remaining minced onion, remaining garlic powder, 1 TBSP olive oil, and ½ TBSP @white wine vinegar{5%tsp} (2 TBSP olive oil and 1 TBSP vinegar for 4 servings) to bowl.

Stir to combine; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Curry Sauce ==

In a second small bowl, combine @vegan mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, remaining garam masala, ½ tsp vinegar (1 tsp for 4 servings), and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4). (Be sure to measure the vinegar—we sent more!)

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @peas{4%oz} and a drizzle of olive oil. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide rice and peas between #bowls{}; top with chickpeas and veggies. Drizzle with chutney and curry sauce. Serve.

> When cool enough to handle, thinly slice chicken crosswise (skip slicing salmon!). Top rice and peas with chicken or salmon along with chickpeas and veggies.